## Decisions made
- Student has NO class FK — membership lives in per-term Enrollment
  (slice 9). Avoids two-sources-of-truth drift. (Changed my/the early
  lean; spec was right.)
- StudentStatus enum: all 5 values defined (ACTIVE/INACTIVE/WITHDRAWN/
  GRADUATED/SUSPENDED), only 3 get transition endpoints in cp2
- dateOfBirth @db.Date (reconciled from spec's DateTime) — calendar date
- PII redaction (DOB/phone/email don't leak to logs) elevated to a real
  cp2 acceptance criterion — first slice with real student PII
- cp3 photo handling: free-text URL field with helper text, NO uploader —
  upload is already listed under Phase 1 deferred ("Student photo upload";
  R2 wired for logos in Phase 0). Saves a half-built uploader.
- cp3 pagination: cursor "Load more" button, not prev/next or infinite
  scroll. Cursor returns only forward; simplest UX matching the contract.
- cp3 sort: row order is server `id ASC` (cursor is on id per cp2's
  comment block — keeps cursor stable across status changes). The
  spec/plan mentioned "lastName ASC default"; not chasing that until a
  pilot asks. Search + the admission-number column cover discovery.
- cp3 status transitions live on the detail page, NOT in the edit form.
  The form shows current status read-only with a pointer to the actions.
  Reason: transitions also set/clear *At timestamps; mixing them with
  PATCH would create half-consistent states.

